a. Summary of CWE:
This happens when a program tries to access data outside the limits of an array, which can cause crashes or expose sensitive data.

b. Example C code:

int arr[3] = {1,2,3};
printf("%d", arr[5]);

c. Remediation (fixed code):

if (index >= 0 && index < 3) {
    printf("%d", arr[index]);
}

Explanation:
Always check the size of the array before accessing it.

d. Mitigation and detection:
Use bounds checking, secure coding practices, and tools like static analyzers.
